title: Get started with Markdown, Sweave and Shiny!
description:
This meetup will be about using Markdown, Sweave and Shiny to make yor work reproducible and easy to share with others. We will give an introduction to the three packages which helps you with:

• organizing your code (Markdown)
• create dynamic reports and makes your work easy to reproduce (Sweave)
•present your work to a wider audience and build interactive web apps (Shiny)

Sounds useful? Come to Foo Café and learn what you can do with these packages together with us! Feel free to bring a friend!

Attend here: http://foocafe.org/stockholm/events/2066-get-started-with-shiny-r-markdown-and-r-sweave

Agenda:
18.00-18.45: Intro to Sweave and R markdown by Aminata Ndiaye
18.45-19.15: Mingle and food
19.15-20.00: Intro to Shiny by Nina Lindell

About our presenters:
Aminata Ndiaye is a research assistant in Biostatistics at Karolinska Institutet and Nina Lindell is a data scientist at Sparks.

title: Do you feel R-curious? Join us in the R-ladies Stockholm!
description:
Struggle with data management in R and still haven’t learned TidyR? Come to our meeting and get an introduction to TidyR by our R-ladies Stefanie and Sophie. We will also present R-Ladies Stockholm and our calendar for the rest of the autumn. Feel free to bring a friend!

Attend here: http://foocafe.org/stockholm/events/1962-introduction-to-tidyr

For more info about TidyR: https://blog.rstudio.com/2014/07/22/introducing-tidyr/

Agenda:
18.00-18.30 Presentation of R-Ladies Stockholm
18.30-19.00 Sophie present TidyR versus base R for data management
19.00-19.30 Break with food
19.30-20.00 Stefanie presents the grammar of TidyR
20.00 Mingle and drinks

About our presenters:
Sophie Debonneville is a research assistant at Karolinska Institutet and has studied Bioinformatics at Lausanne University.
Stefanie Möllberg is a Data Analyst at Nepa AB and has previously studied industrial economics at Lindköping University.

title: R-Ladies Afterwork
description:
Long November evenings are perfect for socialising and learning new things. Join us for a cozy afterwork to get to know each other, discuss project ideas, share career experience and talk all things R.

See you soon!

Note: This event is for women and gender minorities.
Where: Whippet Lab & Social Justice Club
When: November 26, 18:00

title: Basics in R package building: user centered problems and solutions
description:
Are you curious about how to think and do when creating an R package? At this meetup we will discuss problems and possibilities in package building and provide a framework of how you can transform your R code into a user-friendly R package.

17.30-18.00: Doors open, mingle time
18.00-19.00: How to go from functions to an R package

Venue: Antler Office at Venue: Wework Regeringsgatan 29, Room 5c.

About: Antler is a global startup generator and early-stage VC. In their program, they help determined people become great founders of successful tech startups, with the vision of building the next wave of tech. Antler is the sponsor of this event and will provide us with snacks and drinks during the mingle.

Presenters:
Nissa Ferm, data scientist and author of the packages "FastrCAT", "rrza" and "fishgutr".

https://www.nissaferm.com/

Elisabeth Dahlqwist, statistician at Statistics Sweden with a background in biostatistics and author of the packages "AF" and "AFheritability".

https://staff.ki.se/people/elisda?_ga=2.159565181.1967102025.1568902248-1602500728.1560417051

All are welcome but please follow our code of conduct https://rladies.org/code-of-conduct/ !

Poster credit to Tyra Lagerberg.

title: Presentation at Ada conference
description:
R-ladies Stockholm will present at the Ada conference at Foo café! Join to see us and other women working in tech and data science!

https://www.meetup.com/foocafe/events/261282629/?joinRsvpYes=true

title: Supervised classification in Machine Learning and workshop
description:
This meetup will give a walk through of supervised classification with machine-learning classifiers applied to real data. In the second half of the meetup you will have the opportunity to try out the procedure on a simulated data set and evaluate the performance of the classifiers.

18.00-18.40 - Supervised classification with ML classifiers

18.40-19.10 - Food and mingle

19.10-19.40 -Hands-on, so bring your laptop!

19.40-20.00 - Wrap-up

Speaker: Annika Tillander is a senior lecturer in statistics at the Department of Computer and Information Science, Linköping University. She is working on supervised classification for sparse and weak high-dimensional data.

Sign-up here: http://foocafe.org/stockholm/events/2169-supervised-classification-in-machine-learning

Material for the hand-on are here:
https://github.com/rladies/meetup-presentations_stockholm
(files: "R_ladies_20190218.R" and " sim_dat.Rdata")

Slides will be available after the presentation.

Everyone is welcome!

title: Introduction to Machine learning in R
description:
Machine Learning: you've heard the buzz, but come and find out what it really is and how to use it in R. We'll be giving an introduction to the basics of machine learning and a short workshop on supervised learning in the popular package Caret.

Attend here: http://foocafe.org/stockholm/events/2154-an-introduction-to-machine-learning-in-r

Agenda:
18.00-18.45: What is Machine Learning? by Maya
18.45-19.15: Mingle and food
19.15-20.00: Getting started with the caret package by Ashley

About our presenters:
Maya Alsheh Ali - Postdoc at Karolinska Institutet. Specialized in image analysis from mamography screening.

Ashley Thompson - PhD student at Karolinska Institutet. Works on applications for machine learning in psyciatric disorders.
